// Managed memory surface.
//
// RawAlloc[T], Slice[T], and Ref[T] are compiler-recognized opaque handle
// types. Their public methods are lowered directly by the compiler:
//
//   RawAlloc[T].new(count)
//   RawAlloc[T].slice()
//   Slice[T].get(index)
//   Slice[T].set(index, value)
//   Slice[T].ref_at(index)
//   Ref[T].get()
//   Ref[T].set(value)
//
// This module intentionally does not define Aura-callable raw pointer stubs.
